post_text: A special thank you for their patience to all of the students and families who have chosen the online learning for this school year. APEX learning is up and running and after talking with Achieve3000, they hope to be up and running by tomorrow. One of the many good things about online learning is that students are not confined to the regular school day or week and despite not starting when the inperson students did, they can work at their own pace and "catch up" rather quickly. Thank you again and if you have any questions please contact Mr. Scott at 363-6661

Baraga Area Schools Online Learning Statement

Any student that has registered with the school and is getting their education through the school’s on-line curriculum options (Achieve 3000 for grades K-5 & APEX Learning for grades 6-12), the school will have Chromebook checkout on Wednesday & Thursday from 2-4 pm. At this time students and their parents will sign the virtual learning contract and get information about classes and how to get into the system in which they are taking them in. If you have any questions or the above times and dates do not work for you, please contact Principal Tim Scott at 353-6661.

post_text:
First day of school –
Student attending face -to-face will report to their advisors classroom at 8:25 tomorrow, September 1st. Their advisors will go over the handbook changes, COVID expectations, hand out schedules and locker numbers, and beginning of the year forms. Senior class will report to Mrs. Lake’s classroom, Junior class will report to room 215, Sophomore class will report to Mr. Johnston’s classroom, Freshman class will report to Mrs. Gallup’s classroom, 8th grade will report to Mr. Davidson’s classroom, 7th grade will report to Mrs. Rinkinen’s classroom, and 6th grade will report to room 209.
We will then run the attached shortened 7 period schedule starting at 9:21.
Students who need schedule changes will need to make an appointment with Tracy in the High School Office to meet with Mr. Scott.
Students attending online instruction – Online instruction is going to start in a few days. Please check the Baraga Schools website under the live feed for updates.

Again, thank you for your patience as we get this all figured out.

post_text:
Below are the instructions for the Grab -N- Go Food.
BAG CONTENTS:
Frozen:
Meatballs
Teriyaki Dippers
Burritos
Omelet
Hot Pocket
Pizza

Refrigerate:
Milk
Juice cups
Vegetables
Cream cheese
Taco meat
Cheese cup
Cheese slice
Cheese cubes
Strawberries
Ham

Directions:
Taco Meat: Microwave in microwave safe bowl for 45-60 seconds
Hot Pocket: Unwrap & cook for 2 minutes in microwave. Or bake at 350 for 25 minutes. Let stand for 2 minutes before eating.
Burrito: Thaw, bake at 275 for 25 minutes. If baking from frozen bake for 30 minutes.
Cheese pizza: Bake at 400 for 15 minutes
Meatballs: Bake at 375 for 30 minutes. Thawed meatballs can be microwaved for 1-2 minutes.
Teriyaki Dippers: Bake at 350 for 7-10 minutes.

Please discard after April 23rd unless frozen.

Please check out our COVID-19 Resource page for the most updated information.

Please be aware of these following changes and notifications:

• The school building will remain closed until the end of the school year. We will continue to meet the needs of our students by providing learning opportunities.

• We will continue handing out food on Thursdays from 11:00-1:00 and new forms will be available on our resource page and social media.

• The office will have new hours. Starting this week the office will be open from 8:00-2:30 Monday-Thursday.

• Scholarships can be dropped off at the main entrance on Thursdays from 11:00-1:00. There will be a drop-box outside for them.

• Kindergarten registration can also be dropped off at the main entrance on Thursdays from 11:00-1:00. There will be a drop-box outside for them.

post_text: As we all do our best to stay safe during this difficult time, remember our medical personnel as they continue working. Experiencing a lack of PPE such as medical masks, Bay Ambulance reached out to us here at the school for assistance. Our STEM class this year has been learning to design and print objects with our 3D printers, so here is an example of the real world problems we can help solve with STEM and ingenuity. This is a 3D printed mask for medical personnel or for personal use that uses a small 4 cm x 4 cm filter material. Filters can be cut out of surgical masks or filter sheets. Our plan is to supply as many of these 3D printed masks as possible for our local medical workers and school personnel. Anyone who is interested in donating or buying spools of PLA plastic to help out in this time of need can contact Richard Sarau at the school (906-353-6664).

post_text: Guess what Baraga students? We miss you. A lot. So we want to plan a car parade around the neighborhood to wave and say hi. If you would like to wave back at your favorite staff member just look at the map and meet us outside. If you are not on our route and still want to see us we have a parking area planned for you! The car parade will start at the school at 5pm this Monday, April 6th. This will be so exciting but we want to make sure we are all practicing social distancing and being safe during this event. Stay in your cars if you drive and just wave from the window. Stay in your yards if we pass your house and be sure to stand at least 6 feet from people. See you Monday! #VikingStrong

post_text:
UPDATE: APRIL 2, 2020

Governor Whitmer has announced today that all Michigan K-12 schools will be closed for the remainder of the year. We know this will cause additional stress on an already stressful situation but our Governor feels this is the best direction to keep families and the community safe. It was announced that all seniors will graduate and all students showing adequate progress prior to the closure will move onto the next grade. State testing has been canceled for the 2019-2020 school year. We will continue supplemental learning for the remainder of the year. All of these resources and updates can be found on our website or app but our staff is still in the development stages of the learning plans for the school and more information will be made available as things are finalized. Please bear with us as we sort through this ever changing information and be assured that we realize there are multiple barriers to this type of learning and we are working hard to meet the various needs of our students.

post_text: As an FYI, our alert system for voice calls does have a slight delay. The delay at the beginning of those recordings is a result of the system's advanced voicemail detection feature. It is awaiting a human voice or beep (from a voicemail) before playing, to ensure that everyone receives the full message. We have added an automated intro to cut down on that pause time but be aware that there still is a pause until it hears a voice. Thank you and have a great weekend.
